===Etymology===
From {{etyl|xno|en}} {{m|fro|siute}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|sieute}} (modern {{m|fr|suite}}), originally a participle adjective from {{etyl|VL.|-}} {{m|la|*sequita}} (for {{m|la|secūta}}), from {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|sequi||to follow|lang=la}}, because the component garments "follow each other", i.e. are worn together.

